Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter South Africa’s main stock index is little changed as of 10:01 a.m. in Johannesburg after gaining and falling as much as 0.3%. Strength among gold producers on renewed haven demand counters weakness among diversified miners. Declines in market heavyweights Sasol Ltd., Naspers Ltd., and Richemont offset advancing banks and retailers. Investors’ appetite for risk is being tested amid concern over virus-related economic threats, as well as stalled U.S. stimulus talks, and as mounting tension between Washington and Beijing weighs on sentiment. NEWS: